<p>A mythological investigation of Egyptian sermons, Biblical scripture as well as Babylonian and Sumerian excerpts led me to the hypothesis that Pi was encoded in the first chapter of Genesis.</p>
<p>For this examination, we will focus only on demonstrable computations and observations with no conjectures or conclusions.</p>
<section id="background" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="background">Background</h2>
<section id="the-language" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="the-language">The Language</h3>
<p>Hebrew is an ancient Semitic language that has been spoken for over 3,000 years. It was originally written using a script known as <em>Paleo-Hebrew</em><sup>1</sup> which consisted of 22 letters and was used until around the 5<sup>th</sup> century BC. Hebrew was primarily a spoken language Israelites used to communicate to one another.</p>
